#HELP_BEGIN

PRAYER TIMES SIMPL+ MODULE — HELP FILE

Module Created by: Jameel Mohamed
Email: jameelm@gmail.com

PURPOSE
This module calculates Islamic prayer times, Hijri date (Umm al-Qura), Ramadan countdown,
Jumah Mubarak message, tomorrow’s prayer times, and optional custom dates. It supports
high latitude adjustments, automatic DST handling, custom color gradients.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
PARAMETERS (FROM SIMPL+)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

Latitude
• Decimal latitude as a string (no quotes)
• Example: 40.7128

Longitude
• Decimal longitude as a string (no quotes)
• Example: -74.0060

TimezoneOffset
• Integer offset from UTC (standard time)
• Example: -5 for EST
• DST adjustments are applied depending on DST_Mode and DST_Region

DST_Mode (Analog Input)
0 = Disabled
    DST is ignored. TimezoneOffset is used exactly as provided.
1 = Auto
    Module automatically applies DST based on DST_Region.
2 = Force On
    DST is always applied (TimezoneOffset + 1 hour).
3 = Force Off
    DST is never applied.

DST_Region 
Selects the DST ruleset used when DST_Mode = Auto.
0 = North America (Canada / USA)
1 = Europe (EU / UK legacy rules)
2 = Middle East (Gulf regions with partial DST history)
3 = Custom (future expansion)

Notes:
• When DST_Mode = Auto, the module checks the current date against the selected region’s DST rules.
• When DST_Mode = Force On or Force Off, DST_Region is ignored.

Method
• Integer selecting prayer calculation method:
0 = Muslim World League
1 = ISNA
2 = Egyptian General Authority
3 = Umm al?Qura (Saudi Arabia)
4 = University of Islamic Sciences Karachi

Asr_Method
• 1 = Shafi’i
• 2 = Hanafi


INPUTS

High_Latitude (Analog Input)
Selects the high?latitude adjustment rule for Fajr and Isha.
0 = None
1 = Middle of the Night
2 = One?Seventh of the Night
3 = Angle-Based (Angle/60)

Notes:
• Only affects Fajr and Isha.
• Only applies when twilight angles cannot be reached.
• Umm al-Qura does not use high?latitude adjustments.

Compute_Custom_Date (Digital Input)
• Pulse to calculate prayer times for a custom date.



-----------------------------------------------------------------------
OUTPUTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

TODAY’S PRAYER TIMES (Serial)
Fajr
Sunrise
Dhuhr
Asr
Maghrib
Isha
• All formatted as HH:MM

TOMORROW’S PRAYER TIMES (Serial)
Tomorrow_Fajr
Tomorrow_Sunrise
Tomorrow_Dhuhr
Tomorrow_Asr
Tomorrow_Maghrib
Tomorrow_Isha

CURRENT PRAYER LOGIC
CurrentPrayer
• Example: "Asr", "Maghrib", "Isha", "Tahajjud"

NextPrayerCountdown
• Example: "Fajr in 08:44:42"

HIJRI DATE (UMM AL-QURA)
Hijri_Date
Hijri_Month
Hijri_Day
Hijri_Year
• Example: "28 Rajab 1447"

RAMADAN Info

Ramadan_Info
• "X days until Ramadan"
• "Ramadan Day X"


JUMAH MUBARAK

Jumah_Mubarak
• Shows "Jumah Mubarak" every Friday before Maghrib
• Blank on other days


Processor_ID
• Processor ID as a string (send this to jameelm@gmail.com for full license)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
CUSTOM PRAYER COLORS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------


OVERVIEW
The PrayerTimes module supports custom color gradients for each prayer.
Each prayer uses two RGB colors:
  - Start Color: used at the beginning of the prayer window
  - End Color: used at the end of the prayer window

The module automatically interpolates between these two colors to produce
a smooth gradient effect throughout the prayer window.

By default, the module uses built-in colors. These defaults may be
overridden by creating a colors.ini file on the processor.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

COLOR FILE LOCATION
The module looks for the following file at startup:

    /USER/colors.ini

If the file exists, the module loads the custom colors and overrides the
default palette. If the file does not exist, the module uses the built-in
colors.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

FILE FORMAT
The file uses a simple INI-style format. Each prayer has its own section.

Example:

    [Fajr]
    Start=0,180,255
    End=0,60,120

    [Dhuhr]
    Start=255,220,0
    End=255,140,0

    [Asr]
    Start=255,165,0
    End=180,65,0

    [Maghrib]
    Start=255,80,60
    End=120,20,20

    [Isha]
    Start=140,90,255
    End=60,30,120

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

RGB VALUE FORMAT
Each color is defined using three comma-separated values:

    R,G,B

Where:
  - R = Red   (0–255)
  - G = Green (0–255)
  - B = Blue  (0–255)

Spaces are optional. Example:

    Start=255,140,0

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

HOW COLORS ARE APPLIED
1. The module loads default colors during initialization.
2. If colors.ini exists, the module overrides the defaults with values
   found in the file.
3. During runtime, the module calculates a gradient between the Start and
   End colors based on the current prayer window.
4. The resulting RGB values are output to SIMPL Windows as 16-bit analog
   values (0–65535).

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

ERROR HANDLING
- If the file is missing, default colors are used.
- If a section or key is missing, defaults for that prayer are used.
- If an RGB value is invalid, that entry is ignored and defaults remain.
- Errors are printed to the console for debugging.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------

NOTES
- The colors.ini file is optional.
- Only values present in the file are overridden.
- The format is intentionally simple for easy editing.


LICENSING

Module will operate in DEMO mode (No time limit). You will get the prayer times for today except for sunrise. If you want to unlock full functionality please email jameelm@gmail.com and send your processor ID and we will generate a license key.

#HELP_END

#SYMBOL_NAME "Prayer Times v1.0"



DIGITAL_INPUT Compute_Custom_Date, _SKIP_;

ANALOG_INPUT Custom_Year;
ANALOG_INPUT Custom_Month;
ANALOG_INPUT Custom_Day, _SKIP_;

ANALOG_INPUT DST_StartMonth;
ANALOG_INPUT DST_StartDay;
ANALOG_INPUT DST_EndMonth;
ANALOG_INPUT DST_EndDay,_SKIP_;


ANALOG_INPUT Hijri_Adjustment, High_Latitude,_SKIP_;


/*******************************************************************************************
  Parameters
*******************************************************************************************/
INTEGER_PARAMETER 
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
	_SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
	_SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
	_SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,
    _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_, _SKIP_,



    Timezone,
	Time_Format,
	DST_Mode,
	DST_Region,
    Method,
    Asr_Method;
	
STRING_PARAMETER Latitude[20];
STRING_PARAMETER Longitude[20];
STRING_PARAMETER License_Key[50];


/*******************************************************************************************
  Parameter Properties
*******************************************************************************************/
#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES Timezone
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        { 65531d , "EST (UTC-5)" },
        { 65530d , "CST (UTC-6)" },
        { 65529d , "MST (UTC-7)" },
        { 65528d , "PST (UTC-8)" },
        { 0d     , "UTC (0)"     },
        { 1d     , "UTC+1"       },
        { 2d     , "UTC+2"       },
        { 3d     , "UTC+3"       },
        { 4d     , "UTC+4"       },
        { 5d     , "UTC+5"       },
        { 6d     , "UTC+6"       },
        { 7d     , "UTC+7"       },
        { 8d     , "UTC+8"       }
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Select Timezone";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES

#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES Method
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        
        { 0d , "MWL (Muslim World League)" },
		{ 1d , "ISNA (North America)" },
        { 2d , "Egypt" },
		{ 3d , "Umm al-Qura (Makkah)" },
		{ 4d , "Karachi" }
		
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Select Calculation Method";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES

#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES Asr_Method
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        { 1d , "Shafi'i (Shadow = 1)" },
        { 2d , "Hanafi (Shadow = 2)" }
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Select Asr Method";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES


#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES DST_Mode
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        { 0d , "Off" },
		{ 1d , "On" },
        { 2d , "Automatic_Set_Region" }
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Select DST Mode";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES



#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES DST_Region
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        { 0d , "North America" },
		{ 1d , "Europe" },
        { 2d , "Australia" },
		{ 3d , "Custom" }
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Select DST Region";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES

#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES Time_Format
    propValidUnits = unitDecimal;
    propList =
        { 0d , "24 Hour" },
		{ 1d , "12 Hour" }
    ;
    propShortDescription = "Set Time Format";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES


#BEGIN_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES License_Key
    propValidUnits = unitString;
    propDefaultValue = "DEMO";
    propShortDescription = "License Key";
#END_PARAMETER_PROPERTIES





/*******************************************************************************************
  Outputs
*******************************************************************************************/
STRING_OUTPUT Fajr;
STRING_OUTPUT Sunrise;
STRING_OUTPUT Dhuhr;
STRING_OUTPUT Asr;
STRING_OUTPUT Maghrib;
STRING_OUTPUT Isha;

STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Current_Prayer;

ANALOG_OUTPUT Current_Prayer_RED;
ANALOG_OUTPUT Current_Prayer_BLUE;
ANALOG_OUTPUT Current_Prayer_GREEN;
ANALOG_OUTPUT Next_Prayer;

STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Next_Prayer_Countdown;

STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Jumah_Mubarak;



STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Hijri_Date;
STRING_OUTPUT Hijri_Month;
STRING_OUTPUT Hijri_Day;
STRING_OUTPUT Hijri_Year;

STRING_OUTPUT Ramadan_Info;



STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Tomorrow_Fajr;
STRING_OUTPUT Tomorrow_Sunrise;
STRING_OUTPUT Tomorrow_Dhuhr;
STRING_OUTPUT Tomorrow_Asr;
STRING_OUTPUT Tomorrow_Maghrib;
STRING_OUTPUT Tomorrow_Isha;


STRING_OUTPUT _SKIP_, Calc_Fajr;
STRING_OUTPUT Calc_Sunrise;
STRING_OUTPUT Calc_Dhuhr;
STRING_OUTPUT Calc_Asr;
STRING_OUTPUT Calc_Maghrib;
STRING_OUTPUT Calc_Isha;

STRING_OUTPUT Processor_ID,_SKIP_;
STRING_OUTPUT License_Status;



/*******************************************************************************************
  SIMPL# Object
*******************************************************************************************/
PrayerTimes PT;
UmmAlQuraService US;


/*******************************************************************************************
  Helper
*******************************************************************************************/
Function UpdateAll()
{
    // Today
    Fajr     = PT.Fajr;
    Sunrise  = PT.SunriseSimpl;
    Dhuhr    = PT.Dhuhr;
    Asr      = PT.Asr;
    Maghrib  = PT.Maghrib;
    Isha     = PT.Isha;

    // Hijri
    Hijri_Date = PT.HijriDateStringSimpl;
    Hijri_Month  = PT.HijriMonthNameSimpl;
    Hijri_Day  = PT.HijriDayStringSimpl;
    Hijri_Year = PT.HijriYearStringSimpl;

    // Tomorrow
    Tomorrow_Fajr     = PT.TomorrowFajrSimpl;
    Tomorrow_Sunrise  = PT.TomorrowSunriseSimpl;
    Tomorrow_Dhuhr    = PT.TomorrowDhuhrSimpl;
    Tomorrow_Asr      = PT.TomorrowAsrSimpl;
    Tomorrow_Maghrib  = PT.TomorrowMaghribSimpl;
    Tomorrow_Isha     = PT.TomorrowIshaSimpl;
    Ramadan_Info = PT.RamadanStatusSimpl;
    }




Function UpdateParams()
{	

    PT.TimezoneOffset = Timezone;
    PT.MethodParam    = Method;
    PT.AsrMethodParam = Asr_Method;
    PT.Latitude       = Latitude;
    PT.Longitude      = Longitude;
	PT.DSTMode		  = DST_Mode;
	PT.DSTRegion	  = DST_Region;
	PT.CustomStartMonth = DST_StartMonth;
	PT.CustomStartDay = DST_StartDay;
    PT.CustomEndMonth = DST_EndMonth;
	PT.CustomEndDay = DST_EndDay;
    PT.TimeFormat = Time_Format ;
	PT.GetProcessor ();
	Processor_ID = PT.ProcessorIdSimpl;
	PT.SetLicenseKey(License_Key);
    License_Status = PT.LicenseStatusSimpl;
	
	
    PT.Calculate();   // FIRST compute today/tomorrow
	
    UpdateAll();   // read values AFTER SIMPL# writes them
  	

 }

Function NextPrayer()
{
	LONG_INTEGER Recalc; 

   // Lightweight next-prayer update
    PT.UpdatePrayerTimes();
    
    
    Current_Prayer          = PT.CurrentPrayerSimpl;
    Next_Prayer_Countdown = PT.NextPrayerStringSimpl;
    Next_Prayer       = PT.NextPrayerScaledSimpl;
	Current_Prayer_RED	= PT.RedValueSimpl;
	Current_Prayer_BLUE = PT.BlueValueSimpl;
	Current_Prayer_GREEN = PT.GreenValueSimpl;

	Jumah_Mubarak = PT.JumahMubarakSimpl;


 }

FUNCTION ScheduleMidnightRecalc()
{
    INTEGER h;
    INTEGER m;
    INTEGER s;

    LONG_INTEGER secondsNow;
    LONG_INTEGER secondsMidnight;
    LONG_INTEGER msToMidnight;

    LONG_INTEGER hoursLeft;
    LONG_INTEGER minsLeft;
    LONG_INTEGER secsLeft;

    h = GetHourNum();
    m = GetMinutesNum();
    s = GetSecondsNum();

    secondsNow = (h * 3600) + (m * 60) + s;
    secondsMidnight = 86400; // 24*60*60 seconds

    msToMidnight = (secondsMidnight - secondsNow) * 1000;

    IF (msToMidnight < 0)
        msToMidnight = 0;

    // Convert to hours, minutes, seconds for console display
    secsLeft = msToMidnight / 1000;
    hoursLeft = secsLeft / 3600;
    minsLeft = (secsLeft % 3600) / 60;
    secsLeft = secsLeft % 60;

    // Polished console output with current time
    PRINT("[PrayerModule] %02d:%02d:%02d | MidnightRecalc scheduled in %ldh %ldm %lds\n",
          h, m, s, hoursLeft, minsLeft, secsLeft);
    
    WAIT(msToMidnight)
    {
        PRINT("[PrayerModule] %02d:%02d:%02d | Midnight reached, recalculating prayer times\n",
              GetHourNum(), GetMinutesNum(), GetSecondsNum());
	    PT.Calculate();
        UpdateAll();
        // Schedule the next midnight
        ScheduleMidnightRecalc();
    }
}

/*******************************************************************************************
  Initialization
*******************************************************************************************/



 PUSH Compute_Custom_Date
{
    PT.ComputeForDateSimpl(Custom_Year, Custom_Month, Custom_Day);

    WAIT (20)
    {
        Calc_Fajr = PT.CustomFajrSimpl;
        Calc_Sunrise = PT.CustomSunriseSimpl;
        Calc_Dhuhr = PT.CustomDhuhrSimpl;
        Calc_Asr = PT.CustomAsrSimpl;
        Calc_Maghrib = PT.CustomMaghribSimpl;
        Calc_Isha = PT.CustomIshaSimpl;
    }
	
}



CHANGE Hijri_Adjustment
{  

 	PT.SetHijriAdjustment(Hijri_Adjustment);
	PT.CalculateHijriOnly();
	
	WAIT (20)
	{
	Hijri_Date = PT.HijriDateStringSimpl;
    Hijri_Month  = PT.HijriMonthNameSimpl;
    Hijri_Day  = PT.HijriDayStringSimpl;
    Hijri_Year = PT.HijriYearStringSimpl;
	Ramadan_Info = PT.RamadanStatusSimpl;
    }


}

CHANGE High_Latitude
{  

 	PT.SetHighLatitudeMode(High_Latitude);
	PT.Calculate();	
     UpdateAll(); 
}


/*******************************************************************************************
  Auto-run and midnight recalc
*******************************************************************************************/

FUNCTION StartTimer()
{
    WAIT(100)
    {
        NextPrayer();
        StartTimer();
    }
}


FUNCTION Main()
{
  	WAIT(1000)
	{
    ScheduleMidnightRecalc();
	}
   	UpdateParams();
	StartTimer();
	    
 }
             
 